## Gotchas
- The `seededRandom()` RNG is already used in `generateLevel()` — use the same `rng` instance for turtle placement (call `generateTurtle(rng, obstacleData)` AFTER coins are generated to not disturb existing RNG sequence for coins — actually it's fine since it's seeded fresh each run with `Date.now()`)
- `regenerateLevel()` must clean up the turtle mesh to avoid memory leaks and leftover visuals
- The slowdown timer must be decremented BEFORE the velocity calculation so the speed change takes effect the same frame the timer expires
- In `updateFalling()`, still return `slowdownActive` and `slowdownTimer` so the UI stays consistent during falls
- The turtle mesh Group should have `castShadow` enabled on child meshes for visual consistency
- Make sure the slowdown indicator is hidden when the game resets (`exitGameOver`)

